# Feature Modules (Lego Assembly)

## Rules

- **One feature per agent task** — no batching multiple BUILD_PLAN feature rows
- **Vertical slice** — logic, view, tests, i18n in one container folder
- **Thin wiring** — composition root (`appBootstrap.ts` / `main.ts`, `GoldenPathApp.kt` / `MainActivity`) ≤10 lines per feature
- **Sequential before Parallel** — after scaffold step 2, parallel agents may run on **non-overlapping** scopes; orchestrator owns BUILD_PLAN + merge

## After every AGENT step

```bash
python3 scripts/agent-run.py watch-agent-gates --once --autofix
```

On exit `1`: read gate JSON + `.cursor/agent-progress.json`; **auto-fix** lint/tests in feature scope; re-run until pass or 3-strike.

On exit `2`: halt and escalate to human; switch to **Debug Mode** per `docs/CURSOR_MODES.md` when root cause is unclear.

## Auto-fix allowed (no human approval)

- Lint, format, type, and test fixes within active feature container + wiring + tests
- `scripts/feature-autofix.sh` mechanical fixers

## Still requires human

- `git push`, releases, disabling gates (`destructive-ops.mdc`)

See `docs/FEATURE_MODULES.md`.
